<TITLE> Milam hails caretaker government for reform efforts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.com) Former US ambassador to Bangladesh William B Milam Wednesday lauded the caretaker government's current efforts to take the nation forward through instituting a democratic process. The South Asia specialist expected that the nation would be backing the government solidly. After a meeting with law adviser barrister Mainul Hosein, Milam told reporters that it was quite a fruitful and informative discussion. "It was a very good discussion but I didn't discuss any specific issue. That's not my business. I would like to know how the new government is working and handling each thing." "I'd tell you these men are working very hard," he said. Mainul told reporters: "Mr Milam is satisfied with the hard work and sincerity of the government." "He praised the current state of affairsthe way things are being handled by the caretaker government. "He assured us of his fullest cooperation in our efforts to re-establish democracy in the country," Mainul added. Milam was the US ambassador to Bangladesh in 1990-1993. A researcher into Bangladesh and Pakistan issues at Washington, DC-based Woodrow Wilson International Centre for Scholars, Milam is considered an eminent expert on South Asia. bdnews
